23/07/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Three smaller opposition parties are reportedly considering a possible alliance. Local media reported Tuesday (22 July) that the Democratic Union, the Socialist Party and the Democratic Alternative might merge to offer an alternative to the two major forces -- the ruling Social Democratic Union of Macedonia and the main opposition party, VMRO-DPMNE.
In other news, talks between the Macedonian government and the IMF mission begin Wednesday. The talks will focus on Skopje's progress in fulfilling commitments under the stand-by arrangement with the Fund. (Dnevnik, MIA, Makfax - 23/07/03)
